{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T18:04:56.044Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bayes' Theorem"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the fundamental mathematical rule that enables us to update our beliefs about the world when we observe new data—it calculates the probability of a hypothesis given evidence by combining prior knowledge with observed data, forming the foundation for Bayesian inference, uncertainty quantification, and probabilistic AI in machine learning, allowing models to not just make predictions but also express how certain they are about those predictions."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Bayes' Theorem — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical formula:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "P(H | E) = P(E | H) × P(H) / P(E)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "P(H | E)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = posterior probability (probability of hypothesis H after seeing evidence E)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "P(E | H)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = likelihood (probability of evidence E if hypothesis H is true)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "P(H)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = prior probability (initial belief about H before seeing evidence)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "P(E)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = evidence/normalization (total probability of evidence, constant for all hypotheses)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[youtube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9RnrYF6EAcA)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Alternative form (for ML):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "posterior = likelihood × prior / evidence"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Or more commonly:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "P(θ | D) = P(D | θ) × P(θ) / P(D)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "θ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = model parameters (hypothesis)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "D"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = observed data (evidence)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/heyam-eleimat_ai-ml-probabilisticai-activity-7375258728842924032-iK-e)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Intuitive meaning:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayes' Theorem reverses conditional probabilities:\n\nNormal question: \"What is the probability of rain given dark clouds? P(rain|clouds)\"\n\nBayesian question: \"What is the probability of dark clouds given rain? P(clouds|rain)\"\n\nThe theorem allows us to go from P(effect|cause) to P(cause|effect) [web:353]\n\n\"This simple equation allows us to reverse conditional probabilities, moving from the effect back to the cause\" [web:353]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The four components explained"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prior P(H)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What we believe before seeing any data\n\nExamples:\n- \"Before testing, I believe this drug has 50% chance of working\"\n- \"Before seeing text, I believe 'can' is more likely than 'Canadian'\"\n- Initial belief about model parameters θ [web:354][web:356]\n\nThe prior represents our knowledge or assumptions before observing data [web:359]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Likelihood P(E | H)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How likely the evidence is, if the hypothesis is true\n\nExamples:\n- \"If the drug works, how likely is this patient response?\"\n- \"If the word is 'can', how likely is this pronunciation?\"\n- Probability of data given parameters P(D|θ) [web:354]\n\nThe likelihood function is the probability density of getting the data that we actually observed, as a function of the value of θ [web:354]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Evidence P(E)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Total probability of observing the evidence (regardless of hypothesis)\n\nP(E) = Σ P(E | Hᵢ) × P(Hᵢ) over all hypotheses\n\nActs as normalization constant to ensure posterior sums to 1\n\nSame for all hypotheses, so often ignored during comparison [web:353]\n\n\"Since the denominator, the evidence, is the same for all classes, we can ignore it during comparison\" [web:353]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Posterior P(H | E)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Updated belief after seeing evidence\n\nThis is what we want to compute!\n\nExamples:\n- \"After testing, the drug has 90% chance of working\"\n- \"Given this pronunciation, the word is 95% 'can'\"\n- Updated belief about parameters P(θ|D) [web:354]\n\nThe posterior probability density is the updated belief after combining prior and likelihood [web:354]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Visual intuition"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayesian update process:\n\nPrior:     What we believe before data\n           [图示: flat distribution]\n\nLikelihood: What data tells us\n           [图示: peak at observed data]\n\nPosterior: Updated belief (prior × likelihood)\n           [图示: shifted toward data]\n\nPosterior = Prior × Likelihood (normalized) [web:354]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 1: Medical diagnosis"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Setup:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Question: What is the probability a patient has a disease given a positive test?\n\nGiven:\n- Disease prevalence: P(disease) = 0.01 (1%)\n- Test sensitivity: P(positive|disease) = 0.99 (99%)\n- Test false positive: P(positive|no disease) = 0.05 (5%)\n\nFind: P(disease | positive)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayes' calculation:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "P(disease | positive) = P(positive | disease) × P(disease) / P(positive)\n\nP(positive) = P(positive|disease) × P(disease) + P(positive|no disease) × P(no disease)\n            = 0.99 × 0.01 + 0.05 × 0.99\n            = 0.0099 + 0.0495\n            = 0.0594\n\nP(disease | positive) = 0.99 × 0.01 / 0.0594\n                     = 0.0099 / 0.0594\n                     = 0.167 (16.7%)\n\nInterpretation: Even with 99% accurate test, positive result only means 16.7% chance of disease\n(because disease is rare: 1% prior)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 2: Naive Bayes classification"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Setup:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Classify document as \"spam\" or \"not spam\"\n\nGiven features X = {X₁, X₂, ..., Xₙ} (words in document)\n\nFind: P(class | X)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayes' formula:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "P(class | X) = P(X | class) × P(class) / P(X)\n\nNaive assumption: Features are independent given class\n\nP(X | class) = P(X₁ | class) × P(X₂ | class) × ... × P(Xₙ | class)\n\nP(class | X) = P(class) × Πᵢₛ₁ᴺ P(Xᵢ | class) / P(X) [web:353]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MAP decision rule:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Choose class that maximizes posterior:\n\nclass = argmax P(class | X)\n     = argmax P(class) × Πᵢₛ₁ᴺ P(Xᵢ | class)\n\n(Since P(X) is same for all classes, ignore it) [web:353]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\"This is known as the maximum a posteriori, or MAP, decision rule\"."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayes' Theorem for parameter estimation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayesian inference:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Instead of finding single best θ (like MLE), Bayesian finds distribution of θ:\n\nP(θ | D) = P(D | θ) × P(θ) / P(D)\n\nPosterior distribution of parameters given data [web:354][web:360]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparison with MLE:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Maximum Likelihood (MLE)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayesian Estimation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Output"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single best θ: θ"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "MLE = argmax P(D"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "θ)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Full distribution: P(θ"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "D)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prior"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No (ignores prior)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes (incorporates prior knowledge)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Uncertainty"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not captured"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fully captured (distribution)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\"Capital is Canberra\""}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\"Canberra (90%), Sydney (7%), Melbourne (3%)\""}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[towardsdatascience](https://towardsdatascience.com/maximum-likelihood-vs-bayesian-estimation-dd2eb4dfda8a/)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"An MLE model gives a direct answer: 'Canberra'. A Bayesian model might output a probability distribution: Canberra (90%), Sydney (7%), Melbourne (3%). It doesn't just answer, it also shows the degree of certainty\"."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Bayes' Theorem matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key applications:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Application"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Bayes applies"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Uncertainty Quantification"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayesian models express certainty in predictions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Medical Diagnosis"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compute probability of disease given symptoms"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Risk Modeling"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Finance uses Bayesian for uncertainty in risk"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Autonomous Systems"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Safety-critical decisions need uncertainty estimates"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Limited Data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Priors guide learning when data is scarce"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Naive Bayes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Text classification, spam detection"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Critical insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"Where Bayesian is most useful: Domains where uncertainty quantification is critical: healthcare (medical diagnosis), finance (risk modeling), autonomous systems (safety-critical decisions), or any scenario with limited data where priors can guide learning\"."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why LLMs aren't fully Bayesian:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Most generative models (including LLMs like ChatGPT) are trained using Maximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE), not Bayesian approach [web:354]\n\nWhy?\n- Huge computational and memory costs with billions of parameters [web:354]\n- Inference would be slower (sampling/posterior integration) [web:354]\n- MLE training pipelines are mature, scalable, and practically \"good enough\" [web:354]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Relationship between MLE and Bayesian"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The unification:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bayesian estimation equation takes on the same form as Bayes' theorem [web:360]\n\nKey difference: we're using models and probability distributions [web:360]\n\nMLE is equivalent to Bayesian with uniform prior (P(θ) = constant) [web:354]\n\nBayesian = MLE + prior information [web:354]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bayes' formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": P(H"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "E) = P(E"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "H) × P(H) / P(E)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Meaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Reverses conditional probabilities from P(effect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "cause) to P(cause"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "effect)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Posterior"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Updated belief = prior × likelihood (normalized)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Prior"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Initial belief before data"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Likelihood"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": P(data|parameters)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Evidence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": P(data) = normalization constant"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Posterior"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": P(θ|D) = full distribution of parameters"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "MLE vs Bayesian"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": MLE = single best θ; Bayesian = distribution of θ"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Uncertainty"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Bayesian captures uncertainty, MLE doesn't"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "MAP rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Choose class maximizing posterior (ignore evidence)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Naive Bayes"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Text classification assumes feature independence"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Medical"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": P(disease|positive) computed using Bayes"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "MLE = Bayesian + uniform prior"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": MLE ignores prior information"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Applications"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Uncertainty quantification, medical, finance, autonomous systems"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, Bayes' Theorem is fundamental even though most LLMs use MLE: it enables uncertainty quantification (showing certainty in predictions), Bayesian neural networks for robust predictions, variational inference in VAEs (approximating posterior distributions), and probabilistic AI for safety-critical applications like healthcare and autonomous systems where knowing \"how certain\" the model is is as important as the prediction itself; understanding Bayes' Theorem is essential for mastering how models can learn from data while expressing uncertainty and incorporating prior knowledge."}]}]}}